			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Doesn't any kind of interpolation introduce some latency into the audio output?<br /><br />For instance, to add a band-limited step into the output, you need to copy more than just one sample to the output; you need to copy a couple of samples before the step, then the step itself, and then a couple of samples after the step. With linear interpolation, you just need to copy two samples.<br /><br />The latency would probably be too small to be noticable, unless you're running at a super-low frequency rate. Plus, the size of the buffer itself would probably introduce the most significant latency.<br /><br />This was an issue that was always interesting to me; is there any way to have zero-latency audio output? (Or close to it)</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
