					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">But you don't need to explicitly run some loop of code 1.78 million times per second, I think that's what's being said here.</div><br /><br />Yeah, exactly. The results are the same. If I did run a loop at 1.78 million times per second, almost all of that CPU time would be wasted. Might as well just calculate how many CPU ticks occur between an APU channel's tick and the next one, and only update the channel's sample that often and the resolution accuracy of it is still maintained because after every CPU instruction it checks if an update should be made and then it happens.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

